                            <comment id="17943671" author="scoba" created="Fri, 11 Apr 2025 19:03:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi! Do you have an target date for releasing a new version of Commons-Configuration2 with the fix for the HOME folder path issue?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;br/&gt;
= Scott Babcock =&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17943680" author="garydgregory" created="Fri, 11 Apr 2025 19:59:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think Rob is working on a release as we speak, which should be able to start tonight after I release Commons IO. So if all goes well, it should be ready in about a week give or take.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;TY both.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17946211" author="scoba" created="Mon, 21 Apr 2025 19:44:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ggregory&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ggregory&quot;&gt;ggregory&lt;/a&gt; Any update on when the 2.11.1 release will be published? I have several of my own libraries that depend on Commons Configuration that are currently broken, and I&apos;d rather fix forward than revert to an older release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17946216" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 21 Apr 2025 20:45:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=scoba&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;scoba&quot;&gt;scoba&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We just canceled the 2.11.1 release candidate #1. We had missed the fact that we have new APIs, and since we follow semantic versioning, we will create another release candidate for 2.12.0. IOW, there will be no 2.11.1 and instead we will have 2.12.0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you for your patience.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17946240" author="scoba" created="Mon, 21 Apr 2025 22:00:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ggregory&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ggregory&quot;&gt;ggregory&lt;/a&gt; Thanks for the update! Hopefully the API update won&apos;t affect my existing implementation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
